**There is no confirmable June 1–5 trading data, and no June 6–7 news indexed.** All four agents independently hit the same recency wall (~May 28–31, 2026) and correctly refused to fabricate. So the report's hard data extends only to the **May 29 confirmed close**; the June 1–5 weekly column is honestly marked **NOT CONFIRMED**, and the report flags that it must be re-run at publication to fill the gap. (This is the same wall last week's W22 hit.)

### The lede
Two **live weekend catalysts** dominate Monday's open: the **OPEC+ 41st Ministerial Meeting held today (June 7, confirmed scheduled; decision not yet published)** and the **still-unsigned US–Iran 60-day MOU** with Hormuz reopening only partially — a single two-sided oil bet. Underneath: equities entered June at record highs (S&P **7,580**, 9th straight weekly gain, VIX 15.3) on Iran de-escalation, but with a hawkish Fed (new Chair **Warsh**, ~60% 2026 *hike* odds, April PCE 3.8%) and **crypto diverging risk-off** (BTC **~$73.5K**, −42% from ATH). The week ahead pivots to **CPI (Wed June 10)** — the last inflation read before Warsh's first FOMC (June 16–17).

